  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "After 22 years my husband wants out and I believe he is seeing someone, but I am still very much in love. How do I get over him? Or win him back?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry to hear that you're going through this difficult situation. It\u2019s understandable to feel hurt and lost when a long-term relationship is in turmoil. Here are some steps to consider:\n\n### 1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**\n   - Allow yourself to grieve the relationship. It\u2019s normal to feel heartbroken and to process these emotions.\n   - Write down your thoughts and feelings. This can help clarify your emotions and what you truly want.\n\n### 2. **Communicate Openly**\n   - If possible, have a calm and honest conversation with your husband about your feelings and concerns. Express your love and your desire to understand his thoughts and feelings.\n   - Listen to what he has to say. Understanding his perspective may help you find closure.\n\n### 3. **Focus on Self-Care**\n   - Prioritize your well-being. Engage in activities that make you feel good, such as exercise, hobbies, and spending time with loved ones.\n   - Consider seeking professional support, like therapy, to navigate your emotions and gain perspective on the situation.\n\n### 4. **Assess the Possibility of Reconciliation**\n   - If you genuinely want to work on the relationship, think about what changes could be made to address any issues. Can you both commit to counseling or efforts to improve your bond?\n   - It's important to recognize that you cannot control his feelings or choices. If he is determined to leave, you may need to respect his decision.\n\n### 5. **Set Boundaries**\n   - If you decide to give him space or he chooses to leave, establish boundaries to protect your emotional health. Allow yourself some distance to heal.\n\n### 6. **Consider Moving Forward**\n   - While it\u2019s hard, begin to think about what your life may look like without him. Explore new interests or reconnect with friends and family.\n   - Focus on building a fulfilling life for yourself, regardless of the outcome of your relationship.\n\n### 7. **Give It Time**\n   - Healing is a process that takes time. Be patient with yourself, and remember that it\u2019s okay to feel a range of emotions.\n\n### 8. **Avoid Obsessing Over His Actions**\n   - If you suspect he is seeing someone, trying to confirm this can drive you further into despair. Instead, focus on your own healing and choices.\n\nUltimately, whether you want to win him back or move on, prioritize your emotional health and well-being. It\u2019s a challenging path, but you have the strength to get through it.",
